WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.086
FRANK:
Previously on Hardy Boys...

00:03.086 --> 00:04.421
Is there anything else you can tell us?

00:04.421 --> 00:07.591
- Those kids went into the woods,
and a car pulled up to the pay phone.

00:07.591 --> 00:09.801
- What kind of car?
- I don't know. Blue?

00:10.469 --> 00:12.888
FRANK:
Smells sweet, like Dennis' jacket.

00:12.888 --> 00:14.598
It's antifreeze!

00:14.598 --> 00:16.850
Dennis was in the blue car,
he was in the trunk!

00:16.850 --> 00:19.102
JOE: Someone's coming.
FRANK: Hide, hide!

00:19.102 --> 00:20.145
♪

00:20.145 --> 00:21.605
I think Dennis was in that shack,

00:21.605 --> 00:24.358
and I think someone in black boots
burned it down to cover their tracks.

00:24.358 --> 00:27.402
[fire roaring]
[panting]

00:27.402 --> 00:28.904
PHIL:
I just want you to know that

00:28.904 --> 00:30.739
if you do go looking
for your birth mom,

00:30.739 --> 00:32.699
I've got your back.

00:32.699 --> 00:34.952
- I used to do this kind of stuff
with my girlfriend all the time.

00:34.952 --> 00:38.539
- Oh yeah?
- Yeah. Well, ex-girlfriend now.

00:38.956 --> 00:40.082
- Okay, cool.

00:40.082 --> 00:43.502
- Any chance you rescheduled that
call with Woodson Academy?

00:43.502 --> 00:45.212
- They're rescinding your acceptance.

00:45.212 --> 00:48.382
Apparently, there's an allegation of
cheating on your entrance exam.

00:48.382 --> 00:50.175
- It's got to be Donald Dukay.

00:50.175 --> 00:53.136
- I honestly have no idea
what you're talking about.

00:53.136 --> 00:56.181
Why don't you go ask
your benefactor about all this?

00:56.181 --> 00:58.475
CALLIE:
I'd like to schedule a visit.

00:59.059 --> 01:00.561
With Gloria Estabrook.

01:04.022 --> 01:07.025
[birds, insects chirping]

01:07.025 --> 01:10.028
♪

01:10.028 --> 01:13.031
[footsteps]

01:28.839 --> 01:31.842
[distorted noises]

01:45.022 --> 01:48.025
♪ eerie music building ♪

01:48.025 --> 01:50.235
FENTON [echoing]:
Hey. Frank.

01:50.235 --> 01:52.613
[Frank yelling]
Whoa! Hey! Frank!

01:52.613 --> 01:55.365
Hey, hey, hey.
[heavy breathing]

01:55.365 --> 01:57.367
It's alright. It's just a bad dream.

01:59.536 --> 02:02.664
Listen, Wilt called. He needs you to
come in early, help with something.

02:03.290 --> 02:06.376
- [sighs] Now?
- Yep, soon as you can, alright?

02:06.376 --> 02:08.170
Just wanted to let you know
before I took off.

02:08.712 --> 02:11.507
- Where are you going?
- Oh, I gotta head back to Dixon City,

02:11.507 --> 02:13.884
fix some stuff with the house
before I put it on the market.

02:13.884 --> 02:16.011
- You're selling the house?!

02:16.011 --> 02:19.223
Our house. The one we grew up in.
With Mom.

02:19.223 --> 02:22.142
- Guys, I know this is hard,
but we've talked about this before.

02:22.142 --> 02:24.436
- You said you were fixing the house.
You didn't say you were selling it.

02:24.436 --> 02:25.771
FENTON:
Why else would I be fixing it?

02:25.771 --> 02:27.272
We don't live there anymore.

02:27.272 --> 02:29.650
It's time to move forward.

02:31.693 --> 02:33.695
- I'm going to Wilt's.
- I'll go with you.

02:37.533 --> 02:38.575
[sighs]

02:39.451 --> 02:42.454
[radio playing]
[door shuts]

02:42.454 --> 02:45.499
- Imagine how they'll react when you
tell them what you're really up to.

02:45.499 --> 02:47.626
- [sighs] What am I really up to?

02:47.626 --> 02:49.169
- Come on, Fenton.

02:49.169 --> 02:51.547
I'm not a detective,
but you're no handyman.

02:54.216 --> 02:55.759
FENTON:
Is that the Demon Queen dress?

02:55.759 --> 02:58.595
- Gown, but yes.

02:58.595 --> 02:59.930
Don't change the subject.

02:59.930 --> 03:01.682
- Cutting that a little bit close.

03:01.682 --> 03:03.392
Demon Queen's gotta be
wearing it Saturday.

03:03.392 --> 03:05.769
- It'll get done. It always gets done.

03:05.769 --> 03:07.980
Been doing this for 10 years,
and I've never missed a deadline.

03:07.980 --> 03:09.523
It's part of my process.

03:09.523 --> 03:11.316
The stressing and rushing, it... [inhales]

03:11.316 --> 03:13.694
brings up my best ideas.
FENTON: Hm.

03:13.694 --> 03:15.988
You sure these shoulder
things are working?

03:15.988 --> 03:18.866
No. [inhales, clears throat]

03:19.283 --> 03:21.285
- They're epaulets...

03:21.869 --> 03:22.870
and they need you.

03:22.870 --> 03:24.997
♪

03:25.497 --> 03:27.499
The boys, not the epaulets.
- I know.

03:27.499 --> 03:29.710
- So, whatever you're doing in Dixon City?

03:30.210 --> 03:32.045
Your boys need you here.

03:32.504 --> 03:33.964
- I'll be back tonight.

03:36.508 --> 03:37.509
[sighs]

03:38.677 --> 03:41.180
[door creaks]
- Shoulder things...

03:41.180 --> 03:43.056
[birds chirping, dog barking]

03:43.056 --> 03:44.391
- I've still got
a couple of houses to hit.

03:44.391 --> 03:45.684
What'd you wanna show me?

03:45.684 --> 03:46.894
- It's just over here.

03:47.728 --> 03:50.647
- Man, graveyards are even
creepier in the morning.

03:50.647 --> 03:53.400
It's the mist. It's like ghost's breath.

03:53.400 --> 03:55.736
- Or farts.
- Ghosts don't fart.

03:55.736 --> 03:57.988
- You think they breathe?

03:57.988 --> 04:00.657
[barking continues]

04:00.657 --> 04:03.660
♪

04:03.660 --> 04:05.871
- Is that your dad?
- Yeah.

04:07.289 --> 04:09.124
I've been here a bunch since I found him.

04:10.125 --> 04:11.793
Never seen anyone else.

04:12.586 --> 04:14.588
Never seen any flowers.

04:15.756 --> 04:17.758
But someone knew it's his birthday today.

04:19.218 --> 04:21.220
Someone who cared enough to bring these.

04:23.430 --> 04:25.432
- Do you think it was your birth mom?

04:26.058 --> 04:28.560
- It's a long shot,
but it's possible, right?

04:29.478 --> 04:30.521
You in?

04:33.023 --> 04:35.359
[shuts car door]
- Are we overreacting?

04:35.359 --> 04:37.069
- What, about the house?

04:37.069 --> 04:38.529
No! It was our home!

04:38.529 --> 04:40.405
- Yeah, but Dad's right.
We don't live there anymore.

04:40.405 --> 04:43.700
- [scoffs] Then, where do we live?
Frank, what? Aunt Trudy's house? Forever?

04:45.536 --> 04:47.704
- Now, you're overreacting.
- Okay, wha--

04:47.704 --> 04:50.999
A little heads up might have been nice.
A chance to say goodbye.

04:51.959 --> 04:53.794
If I knew we were never coming back,
I would've...

04:53.794 --> 04:56.129
taken all the cash
out of my secret hiding spot.

04:56.129 --> 04:57.256
- Floorboard beside the bed?

04:57.256 --> 04:59.883
- Nah, that's my decoy spot. Sucker.

05:00.342 --> 05:02.261
TEEN: Demon Week, losers!
[laughter]

05:02.261 --> 05:05.013
♪

05:05.013 --> 05:08.475
[grunting, splattering]
[teens laughing]

05:08.475 --> 05:10.936
[car doors slam, tires squeal]

05:10.936 --> 05:12.563
[honking]

05:14.815 --> 05:16.316
[door bell jingling]

05:18.318 --> 05:19.987
[sighs]
[door shuts, bell jingles]

05:20.362 --> 05:23.991
- What happened?
- I could ask you the same thing. Here.

05:25.826 --> 05:27.661
[motorcycle passing]

05:27.661 --> 05:29.580
- So, is this normal?

05:30.330 --> 05:32.958
- That's tradition.
- You call the cops?

05:32.958 --> 05:35.377
WILT:
Ah, it's just kids messing around. I mean,

05:35.377 --> 05:38.589
things always get a little wild
leading up to Demon Day.

05:39.339 --> 05:41.508
Never been broken into before, though.

05:42.092 --> 05:43.260
Eh, what are you going to do?

05:43.260 --> 05:45.637
- I mean, you could get a security system.

05:45.637 --> 05:47.556
Isn't there, like,
an alarm company right next door?

05:47.556 --> 05:49.600
- I remember when you didn't
even have to lock your doors

05:49.600 --> 05:52.561
in this town.
- Yeah, why would you want to do that?

05:52.561 --> 05:54.479
- [sighs] Here.

05:54.479 --> 05:56.273
I'll get another broom.

05:57.274 --> 06:00.027
- I don't work here.
Do you have any rags back there?

06:02.279 --> 06:03.530
[bumps chair]

06:04.072 --> 06:05.115
[door bell jingling]

06:05.115 --> 06:07.284
- Ch, ch, ch-ch... Yo...

06:08.952 --> 06:11.163
[bell jingling]
[laughs]

06:11.955 --> 06:13.582
Demon Week massacre, huh?

06:13.582 --> 06:15.876
- Yeah, I think your smoothie's
gonna take a little longer today.

06:15.876 --> 06:17.669
- [laughs] I can wait.

06:17.669 --> 06:20.047
- You wanna help me move
this back to where it was? [sighs]

06:20.047 --> 06:23.342
- Yeah, okay. Sorry, I missed
wrestling last night.

06:23.342 --> 06:24.718
Not that you were there to notice.

06:24.718 --> 06:27.971
- [grunts] It's all good.
I was doing case stuff. Where were you?

06:27.971 --> 06:29.890
- Got caught up with Belinda.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.600
- Oh yeah?
- Relax. We're just friends.

06:31.600 --> 06:33.435
[laughs]
[door bell jingles, footsteps]

06:33.435 --> 06:36.396
♪

06:36.396 --> 06:37.397
[distorted step]

06:38.232 --> 06:41.360
[distorted noises,
match lighting, flame roars]

06:41.360 --> 06:42.236
MAN [echoing]:
Do you have my order?

06:43.779 --> 06:45.405
Kid, are you listening to me?

06:45.405 --> 06:47.157
I came here to pick up my order.

06:47.157 --> 06:49.159
Wilt keeps it under the counter for me.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.248
- I'll check.

07:04.550 --> 07:07.845
[paper bag crinkling]

07:10.264 --> 07:11.306
Nice boots.

07:16.937 --> 07:18.939
[clipboard clicking]

07:21.942 --> 07:24.945
[drops pen]
[paper bag crinkling]

07:27.573 --> 07:29.616
[door opening]

07:30.534 --> 07:31.577
[door shuts, bell jingling]

07:33.871 --> 07:34.997
- Dude, what was that about?

07:37.207 --> 07:38.834
- That's our prime suspect.

07:39.543 --> 07:42.546
♪ theme song playing ♪

07:54.600 --> 07:57.102
- Are you serious?
You guys know who that is?

07:59.021 --> 08:01.690
- Order says Tom Elroy.
- Yeah, he's the Widowmaker.

08:03.442 --> 08:05.652
Rumor has it he does the bidding
for the Bridgeport Demon.

08:05.652 --> 08:07.946
- Thought you didn't believe in the demon.
CHET: Okay, I don't,

08:07.946 --> 08:09.239
but doesn't mean I have heard stories

08:09.239 --> 08:11.241
about the guy burying bodies
in the East Woods.

08:11.241 --> 08:13.410
- Don't be ridiculous.

08:13.410 --> 08:14.745
The Demon lives in the West Woods.

08:15.204 --> 08:17.956
- [sighs] Come on, man.
- You know Tom Elroy?

08:18.290 --> 08:20.209
- [grunts] Not really.

08:20.209 --> 08:22.628
He picks up his groceries
and never says very much.

08:23.337 --> 08:24.880
- How come I've never seen him before?

08:24.880 --> 08:27.132
- He comes in before we open.

08:27.132 --> 08:28.926
Eh, bit of a recluse, I guess.

08:28.926 --> 08:31.428
Spends most of his time in the woods.

08:31.428 --> 08:33.347
- The East Woods.
WILT: Yeah.

08:33.347 --> 08:35.349
Actually, he owns most of it.

08:35.807 --> 08:37.976
Did you hear about the fire
up there last night?

08:38.769 --> 08:40.771
I guess his hunting shack burned down.

08:40.771 --> 08:43.774
♪

08:43.774 --> 08:46.652
[street chatter]

08:46.652 --> 08:47.653
[door bell ringing]

08:47.653 --> 08:49.029
- Hey, you forgot your lunch again.

08:49.029 --> 08:50.906
- Aw, you're the best.

08:51.865 --> 08:54.076
Hey, here, take a look at this.

08:54.076 --> 08:56.078
[radio playing]
[Callie sighs]

08:56.078 --> 08:57.829
- Can we afford to not charge tax?

08:57.829 --> 09:00.832
- Come on. Where's your Demon Week spirit?

09:00.832 --> 09:03.252
- Exorcised years ago. Bye, Dad.

09:03.252 --> 09:06.088
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
You still want Chinese tonight?

09:06.088 --> 09:07.381
- Oh.
- Inventory.

09:07.381 --> 09:08.924
Now look, it's gonna be a slog,

09:08.924 --> 09:11.677
so I figure we splurge
and we have chicken balls.

09:11.677 --> 09:15.013
- I-I forgot I have to do
prep school stuff with Frank tonight.

09:15.013 --> 09:18.100
- I thought Frank declined Rosewood
same time you did.

09:18.100 --> 09:20.060
- Rosegrave, and he did.

09:20.060 --> 09:22.396
He's just, um, helping me
with-with some stuff now.

09:22.396 --> 09:24.773
- Well, next time you ditch me,
do it for something fun.

09:24.773 --> 09:26.775
- Work now, fun later, right?

09:28.443 --> 09:30.070
[door opens, bell rings]

09:30.070 --> 09:31.822
BIFF: Is this Port Florals?

09:31.822 --> 09:33.657
Did you sell any...
- Carnations.

09:33.657 --> 09:35.576
- ...carnations today?

09:35.576 --> 09:38.829
Oh wow, that many, huh?
Do you remember if you sold any

09:38.829 --> 09:41.039
to a college-educated woman
with a kind disposition?

09:41.039 --> 09:44.501
Caucasian, 33 years old,
dark, curly hair with brown eyes?

09:45.169 --> 09:47.337
Really? Do you know her name?

09:48.130 --> 09:49.965
I saw her drop them when
she was getting into her car,

09:49.965 --> 09:51.800
and I really wanna return them.
- [whispers]: You didn't.

09:51.800 --> 09:54.219
- Sure. Call me back. My name's Joe,

09:54.219 --> 09:56.180
and I'm in the book under Gertrude Hardy.

09:56.180 --> 09:58.515
You can leave a message on the machine
or with my secretary, Trudy,

09:58.515 --> 10:00.309
if I'm not there.
- [mouthing]: Your secretary?

10:00.309 --> 10:02.644
- Okay, thanks. Bye.
[hangs up]

10:02.644 --> 10:04.980
♪

10:04.980 --> 10:07.191
- I have so many questions.

10:07.191 --> 10:09.610
- Can't risk them calling my house
and my mom answering.

10:09.610 --> 10:10.736
- How'd you know about--

10:10.736 --> 10:12.738
- I have a box of adoption stuff,
and this was in it.

10:15.199 --> 10:17.284
It's a non-identifying document.

10:17.284 --> 10:19.453
It's this weird thing they do
for closed adoptions.

10:19.453 --> 10:21.580
Gives you a bunch of information
about your birth parents

10:21.580 --> 10:23.957
without actually revealing who they are.
[opens locker]

10:23.957 --> 10:25.876
It's pretty much a dead end until...

10:25.876 --> 10:27.878
- Flowers at the grave. Got it.

10:27.878 --> 10:29.505
But, how'd you find your dad?

10:29.505 --> 10:31.590
- He wrote a letter to my mom.

10:31.590 --> 10:33.008
To thank her.

10:33.008 --> 10:35.427
He wasn't supposed to, but he signed it.

10:35.427 --> 10:38.805
- Ah, so he's a rule breaker, huh?
Kind of reminds me of someone.

10:38.805 --> 10:41.850
- Guys. Okay, you ready for this?
Remember the plan.

10:41.850 --> 10:44.144
Nobody goes too hard on Lucy.
We play it like we don't know she lied.

10:46.522 --> 10:48.565
What?
- Demon Week?

10:48.565 --> 10:51.443
- Yeah, yeah. Your town sucks, alright?
[Phil laughs]

10:52.986 --> 10:54.238
BIFF:
Did you get the license plate?

10:54.238 --> 10:56.448
- No, my eyes were a little too
full of paint to see the plates.

10:56.448 --> 10:58.617
PHIL:
You think that's the car that got Dennis?

10:58.617 --> 10:59.993
- Doubt it.
They'd have to be pretty dumb

10:59.993 --> 11:01.995
to go pranking a car used to kidnap a kid.

11:01.995 --> 11:03.914
♪

11:03.914 --> 11:05.415
Hey, Dennis?

11:06.708 --> 11:07.876
Remember this?

11:08.502 --> 11:11.213
DENNIS:
My pin. Where'd you find it?

11:11.213 --> 11:14.132
- Hard to explain. Was thinking
I could show you at lunch?

11:14.132 --> 11:16.802
- No, I-I can't. I'm working on my film.

11:16.802 --> 11:18.095
- After school then?

11:18.095 --> 11:20.264
- Still working on the film.
BIFF: Look,

11:20.264 --> 11:23.684
you still need an ending, right?
Joe's got a 35mm.

11:23.684 --> 11:26.353
Just go back to the East Woods
and get the final shots you need.

11:27.312 --> 11:30.023
- Hm. That actually might work.

11:30.023 --> 11:32.526
Shoot some stills, add a voiceover,

11:32.526 --> 11:35.821
do, like, a cool mixed media
avant garde thing.

11:35.821 --> 11:36.947
Very "new wave."

11:36.947 --> 11:40.242
- Oh my god. [grunts]
I mean, yeah, that sounds amazing.

11:40.242 --> 11:41.910
You could time-lapse the sunset--
- No.

11:42.452 --> 11:45.289
- Cool. So, we're all set then.

11:45.289 --> 11:47.666
See you after school?
- I'll come along, too.

11:49.418 --> 11:51.753
- Great. More the merrier.

11:51.753 --> 11:53.297
MUNDER:
Alright. Sit down, everyone.

11:53.297 --> 11:55.716
The quick brown fox isn't gonna jump over

11:55.716 --> 11:57.259
the lazy dog on its own.

12:00.220 --> 12:02.848
TEACHER:
Okay! What I'd like you all to consider

12:02.848 --> 12:04.933
are the internal factors.

12:04.933 --> 12:06.852
Let's delve into
Florian's inner journey...

12:06.852 --> 12:09.563
- [quietly]: Why would the Widowmaker
burn down his own shack?

12:09.563 --> 12:10.731
- [quietly]: To cover his tracks.

12:10.731 --> 12:13.609
Me and Chet are going up to
Tom Elroy's farm after school.

12:13.609 --> 12:15.485
Check it out. You in?

12:16.278 --> 12:17.613
- Um...

12:17.613 --> 12:20.574
No, I-I promised my dad I'd help him
at the store tonight.

12:20.574 --> 12:21.783
He's swamped with inventory.

12:21.783 --> 12:24.620
- Okay. We'll all catch up after.

12:24.620 --> 12:27.831
- Um, no, I'll be there till late.
I'll just see you tomorrow.

12:27.831 --> 12:29.333
- [sighs] Okay.

12:33.712 --> 12:35.214
Is everything alright, Cal?

12:36.048 --> 12:38.050
- Yeah, totally.

12:38.050 --> 12:41.053
♪

12:41.053 --> 12:44.139
So, um, is everything
good with you and Chet?

12:44.723 --> 12:46.225
- Yeah, why wouldn't it be?

12:49.061 --> 12:50.646
Because of me and you? No.

12:52.147 --> 12:54.775
- I mean, he's never said anything.

12:54.775 --> 12:56.485
- Have you?

12:56.485 --> 12:57.486
[bell ringing]
TEACHER: Okay,

12:57.486 --> 13:00.781
I want those on my desk
tomorrow, everyone!

13:00.781 --> 13:01.823
- I'll see you later.

13:02.783 --> 13:05.786
[class chatter]

13:06.578 --> 13:08.080
[birds chirping]

13:12.292 --> 13:14.294
You know we could have taken my car.
- [laughs] No.

13:15.462 --> 13:17.172
I've seen the way you drive.
[Frank chuckles]

13:21.301 --> 13:23.095
- Hey, do we need to, like,

13:23.095 --> 13:25.013
talk about anything?

13:25.013 --> 13:26.348
- Like what?

13:27.015 --> 13:29.226
- [clears throat] Me and Callie.

13:30.561 --> 13:32.187
Things ended kind of
weird between you two.

13:32.187 --> 13:33.814
- You want to talk about this right now?

13:34.898 --> 13:37.276
It was six months ago.
That's longer than we dated.

13:38.318 --> 13:39.444
- Right.

13:40.445 --> 13:41.530
So, we're good.

13:41.530 --> 13:43.782
- I broke up with her, right?

13:43.782 --> 13:45.534
So, there's nothing to talk about.

13:49.621 --> 13:50.998
- What's going on with you and Belinda?

13:50.998 --> 13:53.625
- Also nothing to talk about.
[Frank laughs]

13:54.626 --> 13:55.711
- [quietly]: Wait, there he is.

13:55.711 --> 13:56.712
[door shuts]

13:56.712 --> 13:59.715
♪

14:05.929 --> 14:07.973
FRANK:
He just dumped his trash.

14:07.973 --> 14:09.725
He could be getting rid of more evidence.

14:09.725 --> 14:11.435
Come on.

14:11.435 --> 14:13.645
- Frank, that's... [frustrated grunt]
[door shuts]

14:14.813 --> 14:16.315
♪

14:21.987 --> 14:24.198
So, we're just going to root
through this guy's garbage?

14:24.198 --> 14:26.700
- No. We're gonna steal it and then
root through it someplace safe.

14:44.343 --> 14:45.302
♪

14:45.302 --> 14:47.721
[distorted noises, fire roaring]

14:47.721 --> 14:50.724
[dog barking]

14:54.144 --> 14:55.646
[barking continues]

14:57.189 --> 14:58.232
- What is it?

14:59.566 --> 15:01.276
- Dennis was moved in a blue car.

15:01.276 --> 15:03.946
- Great. Come on. We have to get out of
here before he hears us and comes back.

15:04.738 --> 15:07.741
[barking]

15:11.370 --> 15:12.913
[birds chirping]

15:12.913 --> 15:15.123
- [quietly]: Remind me again
why we're slow-rolling this.

15:15.123 --> 15:16.834
We know Lucy was here.
Why not just call her on it?

15:16.834 --> 15:19.002
- Yeah, but it's better if Dennis
remembers she was here.

15:19.002 --> 15:20.254
That way, she can't deny it.

15:20.254 --> 15:22.589
- You think she bashed him
on the head and left him for dead?

15:22.589 --> 15:24.258
- I think treasure.

15:24.258 --> 15:25.467
- What?
- Think about it.

15:25.467 --> 15:27.761
The two lovebirds come up
to do some filming.

15:27.761 --> 15:30.347
They end up stumbling upon
some treasure. Uh, jewels,

15:30.347 --> 15:32.474
big bag of cash, uh, gold bars.

15:32.474 --> 15:35.561
They plan to split it. She gets greedy.
He gets whacked across the head.

15:35.561 --> 15:37.896
He doesn't remember.
Lucky Lucy, huh?

15:37.896 --> 15:39.898
- Yeah, I guarantee you
that's not what happened.

15:39.898 --> 15:41.149
- Zeros.

15:42.484 --> 15:44.111
JOE:
Hey, guys, what are you doing?

15:44.111 --> 15:45.612
Thought we were going this way.

15:45.612 --> 15:47.239
- No, we're not.

15:47.990 --> 15:51.243
He was filming sunset.
The ridge is this way.

15:51.243 --> 15:53.412
- Yeah, but this is the way to the hunting
shack where we found his pin.

15:53.412 --> 15:54.413
♪

15:54.413 --> 15:56.081
- What are they talking about?

15:56.081 --> 15:57.124
- I don't know.

15:57.916 --> 16:00.335
- What if you never made it
to Sunset Ridge?

16:01.211 --> 16:04.256
Or what if, on the way back,
you ran into something.

16:05.048 --> 16:06.091
Or someone.

16:07.009 --> 16:09.428
Okay, look around. Try to remember.

16:13.599 --> 16:15.350
- I remember feeling sick.

16:15.350 --> 16:17.227
- You weren't alone that night, were you?

16:18.520 --> 16:19.771
Look around.

16:20.772 --> 16:22.774
Who was with you?
- Stop it.

16:24.484 --> 16:26.236
- Look through the lens of the camera.

16:26.236 --> 16:27.446
See if that might help.

16:27.446 --> 16:29.406
- You don't have to do that.

16:31.742 --> 16:34.119
[buttons click, beep]

16:36.580 --> 16:38.790
♪ ominous music ♪

16:38.790 --> 16:40.292
- I remember a red light.

16:41.210 --> 16:42.252
- From the camera?

16:43.837 --> 16:45.714
Or was it brake lights?

16:45.714 --> 16:48.342
You were in the trunk of a car. That's
how you got from here to the Old Mill.

16:48.884 --> 16:50.886
- What are you talking about?
- What about your drawings?

16:51.637 --> 16:53.222
What do those lightning bolts mean?

16:53.222 --> 16:55.224
ELROY:
I knew you'd be back here!

16:56.892 --> 16:59.019
I know what you did, Dennis!

16:59.019 --> 17:01.063
PHIL: It's the Widowmaker!
BIFF: Run!

17:01.063 --> 17:02.523
- I know what you did!

17:02.523 --> 17:04.650
LUCY: Dennis!
- Run!

17:04.650 --> 17:07.694
♪

17:09.696 --> 17:12.324
♪

17:12.324 --> 17:14.910
[panting]

17:18.664 --> 17:20.582
BIFF:
I think we lost him.

17:20.582 --> 17:22.084
- What the hell was that?

17:22.084 --> 17:24.253
- Why was that guy yelling at me?
PHIL: He wasn't just yelling at you.

17:24.253 --> 17:26.463
He knew you.
JOE: He said,

17:26.463 --> 17:27.965
"I knew you'd be back.

17:29.091 --> 17:31.093
I know what you did."
Dennis...

17:32.469 --> 17:34.263
what did you do?
- I can't remember!

17:34.263 --> 17:36.139
And every time I try
to remember, it hurts.

17:36.139 --> 17:37.808
- Well, try harder!
- I said it hurts!

17:37.808 --> 17:39.142
- Back off, Joe!
[Dennis groans]

17:39.142 --> 17:41.770
- Why don't you want him to remember
what happened that night?

17:41.770 --> 17:43.230
LUCY:
Nothing happened.

17:43.605 --> 17:46.733
He was in the woods, and he hit his head.
End of story.

17:46.733 --> 17:49.278
JOE: That's not the end of the story,
and you know it, Lucy.

17:49.278 --> 17:50.279
DENNIS: Stop...
- You know,

17:50.279 --> 17:52.489
where exactly were you
when he "hit his head"?

17:52.489 --> 17:54.157
- Stop, stop, stop, stop it!

17:54.157 --> 17:56.159
[heavy breathing]

17:58.745 --> 18:01.874
- That's it! We're done
with your little mystery game.

18:01.874 --> 18:05.252
♪

18:22.978 --> 18:24.479
- What was that?

18:26.607 --> 18:28.233
- Bad cop.

18:29.985 --> 18:32.988
- We found this in Tom Elroy's trash.

18:34.990 --> 18:36.867
It's a receipt for a power cord

18:36.867 --> 18:38.911
for an RA-150 camcorder.

18:38.911 --> 18:41.538
- That's the AV Club's cam--
That's the AV Club's camera,

18:41.538 --> 18:44.249
the one Dennis lost.
- I knew Tom was our guy.

18:44.249 --> 18:46.585
Black boots, blue car. Guys,

18:46.585 --> 18:48.629
if Tom's buying this power cord,

18:48.629 --> 18:50.756
it means he has the camera.
If he has the camera,

18:50.756 --> 18:53.091
then he has the tape.

18:53.091 --> 18:54.885
We get our hands on that tape,

18:54.885 --> 18:57.054
and we figure out exactly what
happened to Dennis that night.

18:57.054 --> 18:58.305
- How are we going to get ahold of it?

18:58.305 --> 19:00.390
- We're gonna break into Tom's place
and we're gonna steal it.

19:00.891 --> 19:02.142
- That's what I was afraid of.

19:02.142 --> 19:03.477
- Yeah, I love a good break-in,

19:03.477 --> 19:05.521
but all you have is
circumstantial evidence.

19:05.521 --> 19:07.940
- You and Joe broke into
the police chief's house with a lot less.

19:07.940 --> 19:10.651
- But what if there's nothing on the tape?
FRANK: Well we don't know if we don't try.

19:10.651 --> 19:13.946
Guys, this tape is the key
to solving this whole mystery.

19:13.946 --> 19:17.824
So, we can go around in circles,
poking holes in my theory,

19:17.824 --> 19:20.244
or we can quit wasting time and go get it.

19:20.244 --> 19:22.871
♪

19:22.871 --> 19:24.581
JOE:
Frank, just wait, wait!

19:24.581 --> 19:26.792
Are you sure about this?
- Absolutely.

19:26.792 --> 19:29.127
This is all making sense.
- I know. I just--

19:29.127 --> 19:32.130
I went full-steam ahead on Dennis earlier
and it didn't exactly go as planned.

19:32.798 --> 19:35.509
- Joe, The Eye is pointing us
right to Tom Elroy.

19:36.301 --> 19:37.553
Trust me.

19:41.181 --> 19:43.600
Alright, so is it just me and Joe,
or are we all doing this?

19:44.768 --> 19:46.979
- He was right about the car
and the shack.

19:47.938 --> 19:49.439
This is our best shot at the tape.

19:50.899 --> 19:52.359
I trust him.

19:53.485 --> 19:54.987
- Me, too.

19:55.571 --> 19:57.573
- Sure. Why not?

20:00.242 --> 20:03.120
- Okay, fine, fine.
I'm in, but I'm the driver.

20:03.120 --> 20:05.163
Okay, the driver stays in the car.

20:05.163 --> 20:07.124
- Great. Everybody listen up

20:07.124 --> 20:09.710
'cause we only get one shot at this,
and we got to make it work.

20:09.710 --> 20:10.794
♪ Go! by Tones On Tail ♪

20:10.794 --> 20:12.629
Tom Elroy's farm...

20:12.629 --> 20:14.131
is big,

20:14.131 --> 20:17.426
but there's a lot of good cover. Chet?

20:18.594 --> 20:20.012
You're gonna park your car right here.

20:20.012 --> 20:23.557
♪ Living it up,
it's a big kick, it's good for you ♪

20:23.557 --> 20:25.559
♪

20:25.559 --> 20:28.729
I'll set up down here with binoculars,
keep my eyes on Tom.

20:30.355 --> 20:32.608
Joe, Biff, Phil?

20:32.608 --> 20:34.860
This is where you three--

20:34.860 --> 20:36.278
- Get eaten by the attack dog.

20:36.278 --> 20:38.530
- Sorry, what?
- Nobody's getting eaten, alright, Phil?

20:38.530 --> 20:39.823
- Right. Listen, guys.

20:39.823 --> 20:42.701
I know you may think being a paper boy
is all glamor and prestige.

20:42.701 --> 20:44.328
- No one thinks that.

20:44.328 --> 20:46.163
PHIL:
But there's a lot of danger out there,

20:46.163 --> 20:47.789
and I'm really good with dogs.

20:47.789 --> 20:48.916
[barking]

20:48.916 --> 20:50.959
Easy, girl, easy there.
[growling]

20:50.959 --> 20:53.754
- He's gonna be kibble.
- Here, sit!

20:53.754 --> 20:55.005
Who's a good girl?

20:56.298 --> 20:57.716
[rattling]

20:57.716 --> 20:58.759
BIFF: Come on!
PHIL: Here, baby.

20:58.759 --> 21:01.470
Hop in the truck!
[barks, whines]

21:02.179 --> 21:03.805
FRANK:
Once you get the dog, you head to Wilt's.

21:03.805 --> 21:05.849
Call Tom Elroy,
tell him you found his dog,

21:05.849 --> 21:07.809
lure him there.
- Why Wilt's?

21:07.809 --> 21:10.896
FRANK: This guy's a recluse,
but we know he's comfortable at Wilt's.

21:10.896 --> 21:14.525
Also, it's a public place, and we don't
know what this guy is capable of yet.

21:15.108 --> 21:17.361
♪ 'Cause living it up, it's a big kick ♪

21:17.361 --> 21:19.404
- Alright, we're outta here.
See you back at the attic.

21:19.404 --> 21:22.157
CHET: Hang on, hold up.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

21:22.157 --> 21:25.160
I'm doing the job by myself?
Why-why are we splitting up?

21:25.160 --> 21:26.787
- Because Tom saw them in the woods today.

21:26.787 --> 21:28.497
If he sees them again,
he's gonna know something's off.

21:28.497 --> 21:30.332
- Yeah, but he saw me
at Wilt's this morning.

21:30.332 --> 21:31.792
- Yeah, not with Dennis.

21:31.792 --> 21:34.419
Also, I'm happy to switch. If you
want to break into Tom's house--

21:34.419 --> 21:37.297
- No, no. I will make the call
and hand off the dog.

21:37.297 --> 21:39.424
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

21:39.424 --> 21:40.926
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

21:41.677 --> 21:42.678
[tail gate closes]

21:42.678 --> 21:45.514
♪ Ya ya ya ya ya ya ya ya ya ya ♪

21:46.139 --> 21:48.642
[truck door shuts]
FRANK: Once Tom leaves, I head inside.

21:48.642 --> 21:50.018
[truck starts]

21:50.018 --> 21:53.188
Takes seven minutes to get to Wilt's
and seven minutes back.

21:53.188 --> 21:55.190
That gives me 10 minutes to--
- Check your math.

21:55.190 --> 21:57.609
- It's exactly 14 minutes if Tom goes

21:57.609 --> 21:59.695
10 over the speed limit and hits
every green light on the way.

21:59.695 --> 22:01.405
- Twelve would be playing it safe.

22:01.405 --> 22:03.740
FRANK:
Ten's even safer. I head in...

22:04.908 --> 22:08.161
I get the tape, get out.

22:08.161 --> 22:11.164
♪

22:11.164 --> 22:12.082
[grunts]

22:27.472 --> 22:29.433
♪ ominous music ♪

22:31.894 --> 22:32.895
[laughs]

22:35.355 --> 22:36.648
[click, pop]

22:37.482 --> 22:39.484
[sighs] Damn it.
[closes camcorder]

22:41.987 --> 22:44.698
♪

22:44.698 --> 22:47.701
[door buzzing]

22:51.121 --> 22:53.999
[door creaks, shuts, locks]

22:58.337 --> 23:00.839
- Callie. How lovely to see you.

23:02.174 --> 23:03.926
Please, won't you have a seat?

23:10.098 --> 23:12.351
May I offer you some tea?

23:12.351 --> 23:14.937
- This isn't a social call.

23:15.395 --> 23:17.231
- Oh, that's a pity.

23:17.231 --> 23:19.358
Here I thought
we'd have time to catch up.

23:19.358 --> 23:21.610
Bury a few hatchets. [laughs]

23:22.528 --> 23:23.570
[puts down pot]

23:24.655 --> 23:27.074
I hear you're going to Woodson
in the fall.

23:27.074 --> 23:28.325
CALLIE:
I was.

23:29.326 --> 23:31.411
They rescinded my acceptance.

23:31.912 --> 23:34.164
I've been blacklisted from
every prep school in the country

23:34.164 --> 23:36.917
because someone claimed
I cheated to get into Rosegrave.

23:37.501 --> 23:39.461
- That hardly seems fair.

23:39.461 --> 23:41.338
- Did you sabotage me?

23:41.338 --> 23:43.423
- Oh, why would I do that?

23:43.423 --> 23:44.675
[tea cup clinking]

23:44.675 --> 23:46.468
- Because I helped put you here.

23:46.969 --> 23:49.513
- Callie, I've always been
on your side. I still am.

23:50.264 --> 23:52.015
You're a very smart girl.

23:52.015 --> 23:54.685
Besides, you're practically family.

23:55.143 --> 23:57.312
- Then help me clear my name.

23:57.312 --> 23:59.314
I didn't cheat. I aced that test.

23:59.314 --> 24:00.691
- Yes, you did.

24:00.691 --> 24:02.401
- Then why am I being targeted?

24:02.401 --> 24:05.404
I had nothing to do with the corruption
at Rosegrave. I'm not...

24:05.404 --> 24:07.489
I'm not part of The Circle of the Eye.

24:08.115 --> 24:09.741
- But of course, you are.

24:09.741 --> 24:12.744
♪

24:13.620 --> 24:16.206
- What are you...
What are you talking about?

24:16.999 --> 24:19.501
- Everyone aces the test, Callie.

24:21.837 --> 24:24.381
Rosegrave is reserved
for the best and the brightest,

24:24.381 --> 24:27.509
but it is not a meritocracy.

24:27.509 --> 24:28.969
You were chosen.

24:29.511 --> 24:31.805
You were my candidate.

24:31.805 --> 24:34.600
The Circle has many rings,

24:34.600 --> 24:37.853
and you were being groomed
for the innermost.

24:38.520 --> 24:40.772
Your acceptance to Rosegrave,
it was guaranteed

24:40.772 --> 24:43.150
long before you took the entrance exam.

24:44.276 --> 24:46.278
Did you never think it was curious that

24:46.278 --> 24:49.656
of all the prospects, you and Francis
were the last one standing?

24:49.656 --> 24:52.534
My grandson and my protege.

24:52.534 --> 24:54.578
- I never agreed to any of that.

24:54.578 --> 24:55.913
- Yes, you did.

24:57.039 --> 24:58.916
You sought it out.

24:59.750 --> 25:02.961
Our relationship was mutually beneficial.

25:02.961 --> 25:06.423
You needed a-a boost in life,

25:06.423 --> 25:09.343
and I needed to elevate someone
who I knew would be loyal.

25:09.343 --> 25:12.346
Who knows the ends justify the means.

25:12.346 --> 25:14.932
Surely you knew that now?

25:14.932 --> 25:16.850
♪

25:16.850 --> 25:19.645
- I didn't.
- I don't believe you.

25:21.313 --> 25:23.649
That's why you're here. Hm?

25:25.817 --> 25:28.070
You need another boost.

25:29.613 --> 25:32.783
- You don't know me.
- It doesn't matter what people know.

25:32.783 --> 25:35.869
It only matters what they think.
And right now,

25:36.703 --> 25:38.872
you and I are tied together,

25:38.872 --> 25:40.791
whether you like it or not.

25:40.791 --> 25:42.584
So,

25:42.584 --> 25:44.586
why not use it to your advantage?

25:45.587 --> 25:47.881
Fortunately, I'm willing to help you,

25:47.881 --> 25:49.800
but I need your help in return.

25:50.801 --> 25:54.054
I want to mend fences with Francis.

25:54.054 --> 25:55.973
You get him to visit me here,

25:55.973 --> 25:58.725
and I'll put you back on track
for the life you deserve.

26:01.311 --> 26:02.354
- No.

26:03.772 --> 26:05.816
You're not going to use me,

26:05.816 --> 26:07.818
and I won't let you hurt Frank.

26:09.611 --> 26:11.238
I should have never come here.

26:13.031 --> 26:16.952
- Well, perhaps they were wrong
to question your character after all.

26:18.579 --> 26:20.539
I won't be here forever.

26:20.539 --> 26:23.375
If you change her mind,
I'll be glad to help.

26:23.792 --> 26:25.460
And please,

26:25.460 --> 26:27.462
give my love to Francis.

26:28.088 --> 26:31.049
Does he know you're here?

26:33.010 --> 26:35.012
- Go to hell, Gloria.

26:40.267 --> 26:43.270
[insects, birds chirping outside]

26:43.854 --> 26:46.857
♪ tense music ♪

26:58.035 --> 27:00.162
- [sighs] No...

27:02.581 --> 27:03.582
[grunts]

27:04.416 --> 27:05.959
[sighs]
[keys jingle]

27:07.878 --> 27:10.422
[clears throat, heavy breathing]

27:10.422 --> 27:13.008
Come on, come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on, come on.

27:15.010 --> 27:16.386
[heavy breathing]

27:17.971 --> 27:19.014
[sighs]

27:24.144 --> 27:25.729
BELINDA:
Hey.

27:25.729 --> 27:27.356
Cute dog.

27:27.356 --> 27:28.732
- Yeah, he's not mine.

27:28.732 --> 27:31.735
♪ blasting metal from radio ♪

27:33.529 --> 27:34.571
♪ radio stops ♪

27:38.408 --> 27:39.785
[whistling]
[barking]

27:39.785 --> 27:41.495
[dog whining, panting]

27:41.495 --> 27:44.164
- Get in the truck.
[barks]

27:44.665 --> 27:45.958
I saw you earlier.

27:45.958 --> 27:48.168
- Yeah, yeah, I'm here a lot.

27:48.168 --> 27:50.921
I was actually just about to leave,
when I saw your dog

27:50.921 --> 27:53.131
wander around back here, so that's...

27:53.131 --> 27:54.341
pretty lucky.

27:54.883 --> 27:55.968
- You want money or somethin'?

27:55.968 --> 27:58.595
- No. No, I'm just happy I could help.

28:05.936 --> 28:07.437
[starts truck]

28:07.437 --> 28:09.731
♪ metal music resumes ♪

28:15.988 --> 28:17.990
[tires squeal]

28:19.491 --> 28:20.784
I gotta make a phone call.

28:20.784 --> 28:22.452
[phone ringing]

28:22.452 --> 28:25.455
♪

28:26.415 --> 28:28.417
[phone ringing]
[sighs]

28:29.168 --> 28:31.086
Hello?
FRANK: Chet, I need you to stall Tom.

28:31.086 --> 28:33.463
- You gotta be out of your mind.
How do you even have this phone number?

28:33.463 --> 28:34.715
FRANK:
I got it from the operator.

28:34.715 --> 28:36.091
Can you stall him or not?

28:36.091 --> 28:38.635
CHET: Frank, do you really think
he's standing here right next to me?

28:38.635 --> 28:40.387
He's on his way home.
You need to get out of there.

28:40.387 --> 28:41.805
- I know where the tape is.

28:41.805 --> 28:43.473
I need a little more time.
CHET: Frank!

28:46.518 --> 28:47.561
[hangs up]

28:48.312 --> 28:51.315
I-I gotta go.
- Wh-- Go where?

28:52.065 --> 28:54.151
Why are you always running off
to help Frank Hardy?

28:54.151 --> 28:57.070
- Because he's an idiot! Or I am. I...

28:57.070 --> 28:58.864
- Could be both things.

29:01.074 --> 29:04.244
- What are you doing?
- I'm an idiot, too. Explain on the way.

29:06.538 --> 29:08.332
[sighs]
[door opens]

29:09.082 --> 29:10.083
[door shuts]

29:11.502 --> 29:12.794
- Hey, Joe.

29:12.794 --> 29:15.881
There was a message for you
on the machine from a florist.

29:15.881 --> 29:16.924
- What?

29:16.924 --> 29:18.759
- Yeah, about the woman you're
looking for, Abigail Owens.

29:19.384 --> 29:20.719
- Who?

29:20.719 --> 29:21.970
- How do you know Abigail Owens?

29:21.970 --> 29:24.014
- Wait, do you know her?
- Sort of.

29:24.014 --> 29:26.225
I know the name.
She was Demon Queen back in the day.

29:26.934 --> 29:29.186
- She was what?
- Demon Queen, man.

29:29.186 --> 29:30.896
Heroine of the Demon Day parade.

29:30.896 --> 29:33.065
Float and everyone wears masks and cloaks,

29:33.065 --> 29:34.983
and she has this rad sword and gown.

29:34.983 --> 29:37.236
Your aunt designs the gown,
which are amazing, by the way.

29:37.236 --> 29:40.948
- Oh! Thank you. That's so kind.
It takes a lot of--

29:40.948 --> 29:42.699
- Are those epaulets ostrich feathers?

29:42.699 --> 29:44.660
TRUDY:
Yes, actually.

29:44.660 --> 29:46.912
I think it brings a certain menace.

29:46.912 --> 29:49.748
- Can we go back to Abigail Owens, please?
When was she the Demon Queen?

29:50.541 --> 29:52.626
- Uh, about 15 years ago.

29:52.626 --> 29:54.086
- Did you design her dress?
- No.

29:54.086 --> 29:55.838
Sorry, how old do you guys think I am?

29:55.838 --> 29:57.297
- Do you have any photos of her?

29:58.131 --> 30:01.426
- Probably. I've got a bunch of photos
in the garage for inspiration.

30:01.426 --> 30:02.594
What's it for?

30:03.345 --> 30:05.055
- It's for art class.

30:05.055 --> 30:06.849
We're doing a retrospective
on gown fashion

30:07.432 --> 30:10.310
and how it's evolved throughout the years.
- Sure.

30:10.310 --> 30:12.855
- Well you're not in our art class, right?
So that's why you don't know.

30:14.273 --> 30:16.984
- Okay. That sounds great.
I'll go get them.

30:16.984 --> 30:18.235
PHIL:
Thank you.

30:21.655 --> 30:23.657
- Since when do you care about dresses?

30:23.657 --> 30:25.200
♪

30:25.200 --> 30:27.578
Spill it. What's this really about?

30:31.999 --> 30:34.710
[keys jingling]

30:36.670 --> 30:37.671
[door opens]

30:39.840 --> 30:40.883
- Don't move.

30:46.722 --> 30:48.348
JOE:
I'm really sorry, Biff.

30:48.348 --> 30:50.767
If I'd known,
then I wouldn't h-- I wouldn't have

30:50.767 --> 30:52.769
hounded you about your dad.
- I know.

30:53.562 --> 30:55.564
It's okay.
- I know what it's like.

30:55.564 --> 30:57.608
♪

30:57.608 --> 31:00.110
I'm not saying that you had
to have told me. It's just...

31:01.778 --> 31:04.656
you could have.
- You were making it your thing.

31:04.656 --> 31:06.950
It's not. It's mine.

31:07.618 --> 31:10.204
I needed to do it on my own.
- With Phil.

31:10.204 --> 31:12.164
PHIL: It would be a lot easier
to find Abigail Owens

31:12.164 --> 31:13.790
if the pictures were labeled properly

31:13.790 --> 31:15.709
and there was some sort of organization.

31:17.377 --> 31:18.879
- Just sort of happened.

31:18.879 --> 31:20.923
- So, what's this mean?

31:20.923 --> 31:22.508
You're officially searching
for your birth mom?

31:22.508 --> 31:23.926
PHIL:
Guys...

31:23.926 --> 31:25.385
guys, I think I found her.

31:25.385 --> 31:28.388
♪

31:29.890 --> 31:32.059
She's not what I was picturing at all.

31:32.601 --> 31:35.103
I mean, I also forgot she'd be 17, but...

31:35.521 --> 31:37.940
- Wow. So, that's...

31:39.024 --> 31:40.400
- Yeah.

31:40.400 --> 31:42.402
PHIL:
She's beautiful.

31:44.279 --> 31:45.989
- I don't want any trouble.

31:45.989 --> 31:48.492
- Well, you should've thought of that
before you broke into my house.

31:48.492 --> 31:50.160
- I'm here for the tape.
I know you have it.

31:50.160 --> 31:52.246
- You're making a big mistake, kid.

31:52.246 --> 31:54.498
[running footsteps]
CHET: Whoa, stop!

31:54.498 --> 31:56.124
ELROY:
Ah, you got to be kidding.

31:56.917 --> 31:58.293
You punks get bolder every year.

31:58.293 --> 32:00.712
Every Demon Week, you mess
with me and you mess with me

32:00.712 --> 32:02.422
and you mess with me!
Well, I'm sick of it!

32:02.422 --> 32:04.550
- Alright, alright! Just go easy.
No one needs to get hurt.

32:04.550 --> 32:06.969
- You burn down my shack!
You steal my dog!

32:06.969 --> 32:09.429
You break into my house!
CHET: Hey, we didn't burn down your shack.

32:09.429 --> 32:12.432
Okay, this is a mistake.
A bad mistake. We're just going to go.

32:12.432 --> 32:14.393
- I'm not going anywhere
without that tape.

32:14.393 --> 32:16.186
It's in your foot locker. Open it!

32:16.186 --> 32:18.146
- [laughs] You think you're so smart?
- Open it!

32:18.146 --> 32:19.690
- You never should have come here.

32:19.690 --> 32:21.525
- Whoa, whoa, whoa! Hey!
FRANK: What are you gonna do?

32:21.525 --> 32:24.069
You gonna hurt me like you hurt Dennis?
There's three of us here now.

32:24.069 --> 32:25.487
- Frank, cool it.

32:25.487 --> 32:28.365
- I didn't touch Dennis.
I never did anything to anyone.

32:28.365 --> 32:30.284
- Prove it! Open the locker!

32:30.284 --> 32:31.577
- You wanna see what's in the locker?!

32:31.577 --> 32:32.828
♪

32:32.828 --> 32:34.580
[keys jingling]

32:36.248 --> 32:38.292
[unlocking foot locker]

32:40.210 --> 32:42.713
There! You happy?

32:46.341 --> 32:47.885
What's the matter, kid?

32:47.885 --> 32:50.053
It's not what you were expecting?

32:53.557 --> 32:55.058
- You're a war hero?

32:55.058 --> 32:57.269
- I was just young and brave and stupid.

32:58.103 --> 33:00.147
I got myself involved in something
I didn't understand

33:00.147 --> 33:02.065
in a place I had no business being.

33:04.902 --> 33:07.362
I've seen enough death and pain
in my life. I don't hurt people.

33:10.824 --> 33:13.327
Now, why don't you tell me
what you're doing in my house?

33:15.495 --> 33:18.332
- Something happened to this kid
at my school.

33:18.332 --> 33:20.042
Something that he can't remember.

33:20.918 --> 33:23.128
He went missing and we found him
in the West Woods,

33:23.128 --> 33:24.963
but he was in your shack that night.

33:24.963 --> 33:27.758
- He was moved in a blue car,

33:27.758 --> 33:29.092
like the one in your yard.

33:29.092 --> 33:31.678
- Well, that blue car
doesn't move. Has no engine.

33:33.055 --> 33:35.140
Any other smoking guns or is that it?

33:37.100 --> 33:40.020
- The boots. I saw someone in those
exact black boots.

33:40.020 --> 33:41.563
They burnt down your shack. I was there,

33:41.563 --> 33:43.899
I was the one who called it in!
ELROY: These boots are standard issue.

33:43.899 --> 33:46.193
You can get 'em in any surplus store.

33:46.193 --> 33:48.570
Why would I burn down my own shack?

33:48.570 --> 33:49.821
- To hide evidence.

33:50.531 --> 33:51.573
Right?

33:53.242 --> 33:55.285
When I saw you with the camera, you know,

33:55.285 --> 33:56.954
I thought--
ELROY: Yeah, I know what you thought.

33:57.704 --> 33:59.039
I know what people call me.

33:59.957 --> 34:02.584
Widowmaker, Demon Helper.

34:02.584 --> 34:06.046
I just don't get it. I mean,
the Demon lives in the West Woods.

34:06.046 --> 34:07.297
[weak laughter]

34:07.965 --> 34:09.967
BELINDA: But then,
how did you end up with the camera?

34:10.509 --> 34:13.428
- Well, I take walks, plant trees,

34:13.428 --> 34:16.056
pick up trash the trespassers
leave behind.

34:16.056 --> 34:18.141
Found the camera
lying in a puddle of water.

34:18.141 --> 34:20.686
I figured it belonged to whatever punk
burned down my shack.

34:20.686 --> 34:22.312
Battery was dead,
so I bought a charger,

34:22.312 --> 34:24.106
and I tried to watch the tape
to find out who did it.

34:25.232 --> 34:26.692
- So, you still have the tape.

34:26.692 --> 34:28.902
[popping, booming]
[gasping]

34:28.902 --> 34:30.571
What the hell's going on?
[dog barking]

34:30.571 --> 34:32.656
♪

34:32.656 --> 34:34.241
[popping continues]
- Hey! Hey, stop it!

34:34.241 --> 34:35.492
TEEN:
Oh, that's far enough!

34:35.492 --> 34:36.702
[firing]

34:36.702 --> 34:38.328
Oh-ho-ho! Got him!

34:38.328 --> 34:40.205
[dog barking]

34:41.707 --> 34:43.876
[firing continues]

34:43.876 --> 34:45.878
[ears ringing]
[gunfire]

34:47.296 --> 34:51.049
[firing]
[dog barking]

34:51.049 --> 34:52.759
[teens laughing]

34:53.969 --> 34:55.804
[barking continues]

34:57.431 --> 34:59.433
[barking]

34:59.433 --> 35:01.727
[teens yelling]

35:05.522 --> 35:08.192
[barking]

35:10.277 --> 35:13.280
[birds chirping]
[street noise]

35:13.280 --> 35:15.282
[sniffling]

35:15.282 --> 35:18.285
[heavy breathing]
[indistinct chatter]

35:18.911 --> 35:21.914
[car approaching]

35:23.081 --> 35:25.083
[brakes clunking, engine stops]

35:25.375 --> 35:26.585
[door opens]

35:27.085 --> 35:29.671
♪

35:29.671 --> 35:31.006
[car door shuts]

35:32.966 --> 35:33.967
[keys jingling]

35:43.644 --> 35:45.646
[heavy breathing]

35:51.443 --> 35:53.612
- Thanks for having my back, man.

35:53.612 --> 35:55.280
If you hadn't had come, I'd...

35:55.280 --> 35:56.865
Well, I might have done
something really stupid.

35:56.865 --> 35:59.409
- [scoffs] See, I'd argue that
this was really stupid,

35:59.409 --> 36:01.870
but hey, that's just me.
[Frank laughs]

36:02.496 --> 36:05.290
FRANK: Belinda's cool.
CHET: Really cool.

36:05.290 --> 36:06.917
[dog barking]

36:06.917 --> 36:09.419
Okay, don't look at me like that.
I'm not really her type.

36:09.419 --> 36:10.546
- You sure?

36:10.546 --> 36:12.297
[laughs]

36:12.756 --> 36:16.009
- [sighs] Dognapping,
breaking and entering...

36:17.052 --> 36:18.512
demons.

36:18.512 --> 36:20.264
And here I thought
Bridgeport was going to be boring.

36:20.264 --> 36:21.098
CHET:
Oh, it was.

36:21.098 --> 36:23.475
It was really nice and boring,
until this idiot showed up.

36:23.475 --> 36:24.476
ELROY:
Hey.

36:24.476 --> 36:27.521
♪

36:29.857 --> 36:31.400
[cassette rattling]

36:32.776 --> 36:33.819
Here.

36:36.363 --> 36:38.532
I don't know what good it's gonna do you.
I couldn't get it to play.

36:38.532 --> 36:40.158
It's pretty water-damaged.

36:41.243 --> 36:43.120
- You want us to track down
those punks for you?

36:43.120 --> 36:45.581
- No, you guys have done enough.

36:45.581 --> 36:48.584
Demon week's almost over.
They're not gonna be back this year.

36:49.918 --> 36:53.005
- Thanks for everything, Tom.
And if you ever need anything,

36:53.005 --> 36:55.799
just say the word.
- Thanks, kid.

36:57.426 --> 36:59.261
[knocking]
[insects chirping]

37:01.513 --> 37:03.182
[knocking]
[door opens]

37:03.182 --> 37:04.308
- Where's Dennis?

37:04.808 --> 37:06.602
- He's not with you?
- No!

37:06.602 --> 37:09.396
We were editing,
and then I left to go get us some food,

37:09.396 --> 37:11.565
and when I got back, he was gone.

37:11.565 --> 37:13.525
He's really not with you?

37:13.525 --> 37:15.194
- No, but we'll help you find him.

37:15.194 --> 37:16.570
♪

37:16.570 --> 37:19.072
- What? No... [sighs]
- Come on. Let's go.

37:21.450 --> 37:22.492
[door creaks, shuts]

37:23.076 --> 37:26.079
LUCY: This is stupid! I already
checked the school. He's not here.

37:26.079 --> 37:28.457
- We need to retrace his steps.
LUCY: We're wasting time!

37:28.457 --> 37:31.627
He could be anywhere by now.
What if he went back to the shack

37:31.627 --> 37:33.295
because you made him think
he was there that night?

37:33.295 --> 37:35.047
JOE: He was there that night.
- Guys...

37:35.047 --> 37:36.381
- If I had just been there, I could've--

37:36.381 --> 37:38.300
- Are you seriously gonna keep
pretending like you weren't there?

37:38.300 --> 37:39.384
- Guys.
LUCY: You really think

37:39.384 --> 37:41.762
I did something to my boyfriend, Joe?

37:41.762 --> 37:43.096
You have no idea
what you're talking about.

37:43.096 --> 37:44.515
- Guys!
BOTH: What?!

37:44.515 --> 37:47.518
[insects chirping]
[indistinct voice]

37:51.230 --> 37:52.731
- You guys hear that?

37:53.774 --> 37:55.025
[indistinct voice]

37:56.818 --> 37:59.821
[distorted video playing]
[distorted heavy breathing]

38:01.573 --> 38:03.575
[static crackling]

38:03.575 --> 38:06.453
- Dude, what gives?
I've been looking everywhere for you!

38:07.120 --> 38:08.413
Dennis!
[indistinct video chatter]

38:10.165 --> 38:11.625
Dennis?

38:11.625 --> 38:14.127
DENNIS [on video]: Oh my god.
LUCY: Dennis?

38:14.127 --> 38:16.672
[Dennis panting in video]

38:16.672 --> 38:18.131
Dennis?!

38:18.131 --> 38:21.760
DENNIS [on video, distorted]:
Oh my god. Oh my god. Oh my god.

38:21.760 --> 38:24.805
♪

38:26.807 --> 38:29.935
♪

38:29.935 --> 38:32.062
- It's weird. It's like he's just blank.

38:33.021 --> 38:34.690
- Maybe his injury's getting worse.

38:35.732 --> 38:37.359
- Maybe someone got to him again.

38:37.359 --> 38:40.362
[paramedic chatter]

38:53.208 --> 38:55.377
- You really think this is my fault?

38:58.213 --> 39:00.716
- I'm gonna need to see Dennis' notebook.

39:02.593 --> 39:04.595
[Lucy sighs]
Could be a clue in it.

39:06.722 --> 39:08.348
- Stay away from me, Joe.

39:16.190 --> 39:17.191
[sighs]

39:17.191 --> 39:19.693
[insects chirping]
[thunder rumbling]

39:20.694 --> 39:22.779
- I thought I understood what
The Eye was trying to show me,

39:22.779 --> 39:25.532
but I was just cherry-picking
what I wanted to be true.

39:25.532 --> 39:28.368
You know what this means, right?
- We keep trying?

39:28.911 --> 39:31.747
- No, it means that there's room
for human error and bias.

39:31.747 --> 39:34.958
If we put the wrong pieces together,
draw the wrong conclusions,

39:34.958 --> 39:37.002
then there's going to be consequences.

39:38.629 --> 39:40.172
I think we're just lucky no one got hurt.

39:41.465 --> 39:44.176
- Dennis got hurt.
- And Tom was nowhere near.

39:44.176 --> 39:45.177
[scoffs]

39:46.303 --> 39:48.514
I was so sure and so wrong.

39:50.557 --> 39:51.850
[thunder]

39:51.850 --> 39:53.936
Look, we can't just keep
relying on The Eye.

39:53.936 --> 39:56.688
Not until we're absolutely certain
we're drawing the right connections.

39:56.688 --> 39:58.815
- How will we know?
- We're gonna do it together.

39:59.274 --> 40:01.401
You'll keep me in check.

40:01.401 --> 40:03.570
I know you've tried before,
and I didn't listen.

40:03.570 --> 40:05.572
That's not going to happen anymore.

40:05.572 --> 40:07.616
- We gotta crack this thing
before someone else gets hurt.

40:07.616 --> 40:08.867
- And we will.

40:10.244 --> 40:12.246
Using good old-fashioned detective work.

40:13.288 --> 40:14.790
- What do you think you're doing?

40:14.790 --> 40:17.835
- Who, us?
- Uh, we were just, um--

40:17.835 --> 40:20.379
- Don't lie to me.
I know you're working on a case.

40:20.379 --> 40:22.923
- We can explain.
- I don't need your excuses.

40:22.923 --> 40:25.551
How many times do I have to tell you guys?
[thunder]

40:25.551 --> 40:28.554
♪

40:29.096 --> 40:33.016
Never take a player off the board
until the case is closed.

40:33.016 --> 40:35.269
[rain pattering]

40:35.269 --> 40:37.896
- Um, so we're not...
we're not in trouble?

40:37.896 --> 40:40.148
- Nah, I'm not going to pile on.

40:40.148 --> 40:42.109
Trouble'll find you guys sooner or later.

40:43.360 --> 40:45.571
Though it looks like
it might already have.

40:47.281 --> 40:48.407
Is there anything I should know?

40:51.118 --> 40:52.369
You guys are aware that I'm, like,

40:52.369 --> 40:54.454
a world-famous private detective, right?

40:54.454 --> 40:56.790
- Yeah, we've heard.
- Yeah?

40:56.790 --> 40:59.418
- I think we're good.
FENTON: Just be smart.

40:59.418 --> 41:02.838
And when you guys get in
over your head, come see me.

41:02.838 --> 41:05.966
- We will.
- We promise.

41:05.966 --> 41:08.468
- Great. So...
[thunder]

41:08.468 --> 41:10.554
[rain continues]

41:10.554 --> 41:12.639
[sighs] Wow.

41:12.639 --> 41:15.642
♪

41:15.642 --> 41:19.521
If I were you guys, I'd start with,
uh, finding this camcorder.

41:22.316 --> 41:23.567
- Hey! Um...

41:25.569 --> 41:27.112
How'd it go with the house?

41:27.112 --> 41:30.616
- It's coming along, you know. It's just
that it's a bigger job than I thought.

41:30.616 --> 41:33.285
So, gonna be doing
a lot of back-and-forth.

41:35.162 --> 41:37.998
- Well, uh, you just let us know
if you're ever in over your head.

41:37.998 --> 41:39.041
FENTON:
I'll do that.

41:40.292 --> 41:42.920
Night, boys.
[thunder]

41:43.462 --> 41:44.963
FRANK [on headphones]:
Night, Dad.

41:46.381 --> 41:48.383
[thunder]
[click]

41:49.343 --> 41:52.221
JOE [on headphones]: Hey,
maybe we should tell him about The Eye.

41:53.222 --> 41:55.724
Maybe he can help.
FRANK: No.

41:57.100 --> 41:59.394
The more people that know,
the more dangerous it gets.

42:01.188 --> 42:04.191
♪
